<br>
What's a decent class to play? <br>
<br>
Agents any good? Are they hard to level like DAOC archers and assassins. <br>
<br>
How about adventures? Or are they as gimped as Hunters <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Fixers? Sound something along the line as skalds. <br>
<br>
How about martial arts?<br>
<br>
Basically looking for a class that if more on the offensive side, but is not 100% melee (like a tank) or a pure caster. No healers either. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub96.ezboard.com/bdragonknightsdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ci>Ci</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>[GM]</span><br>  Posts: 844<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(12/18/02 9:27:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub96.ezboard.com/fdragonknightsdaocfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.dragonknights.org/ciaaran_head.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looking for advice for AO</span><hr size=1> Well, I am totally biased but I loved playing a fixer. Yes, they are skaldish. But, they also have the best heal-over-time spells in the game. They are not a healer however. They travel faster than any other class - complete with their own transport method (fixer grid). Fixers make decent tanks if necessary and the high end grid armor is pretty damn sweet.<br>
<br>
At level 80 I was able to solo a level 124 mob. Very good offensively and no other class in the game can match a fixer for making cash unless you count very high level tradeskills like nanoprogramming.<br>
<br>
If you do make a fixer go with the SMG/Burst only weapons. Anything else is a waste of time. These would include the low level fixer staple - Mausser Particle Streamer (MPS). <br>
<br>
Assuming you are starting on Rubi-Ka 1 as Omni I could log in  help ya a bit perhaps. I think Ovarrd may be playing a little there also when SWG is a bear to log into.. <br>
<br>
The Enforcer is nice for melee. They do a LOT of damage. <br>
<br>
Martial Artist WAS a great class for damage also - though I hear they nerfed the crit damage and now they are ok.<br>
<br>
Agents are perhaps the hardest class to play since they can become almost any class like a disguise. Which is to say they can actually use other classes skills as well. Interesting class though I never got into it.<br>
<br>
Adventurers - just from listening to other people I could say they appear gimped though I don't know why people say that.<br>
<br>
As you start move your AGG slider to full AGGressive. This will ensure your shooting and casting times are as quick as possible. <p>===================<BR>
